						<div class="postbody">I want the extra work RAM even if it isn't battery-backed, but I also want the save. That's why I suggested that <em>something</em> had to be mapped into $5000-$5FFF, whether it is the control register for an I2C port (for serial FRAM) or a control for write-enabling the PRG ROM (for using a 29F040 as the PRG ROM and saving back to half of that). BootGod's DB lists <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/search.php?ines_op=%3D%60%40%60&amp;ines=16&amp;hardware_op=OR&amp;hardware%5B%5D=24C01&amp;hardware%5B%5D=24C02&amp;field=2&amp;order=asc" class="postlink">six Japan-only games by Bandai</a> on <a href="http://nesdev.com/bandai-e.txt" class="postlink">mapper 16</a> that use an I2C-like serial EEPROM.</div>

