				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I looked up digikey pricing on Microchip EEPROMs on digikey on some sizes and it seems to roughly like this (obviously not a complete list):
<br />
<br />$0.20 256 bytes
<br />$0.40 8kB
<br />$3.14 128kB (largest available)
<br />
<br />I just wonder if there is a good way to get a clock for it.  The trouble I see is that most address decoding will involve PRG/CE, which is already gated with M2 (the clock).  Not sure if that's a problem yet (obviously it's been done before).  There's probably one with an enable, I didn't check.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
